---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Sriman Tirupathy Eshwarappa">
	<section class="container mx-auto px-6 py-24">
		<div class="max-w-3xl">
			<h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-8 text-left">About Me</h1>
			<p class="text-lg text-slate-400 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
				I am a technology leader with over 18 years of experience architecting large-scale integration hub, cloud-native platforms, and AI-driven solutions. My journey has spanned critical sectors from **Healthcare and Telecom** to **National Identity Systems**.
			</p>
			<p class="text-lg text-slate-400 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
				Expert in **MuleSoft (Architect Certified)**, microservices, and API-led connectivity, I specialize in modernizing legacy monoliths into resilient, observable ecosystems. 
			</p>
			<p class="text-lg text-slate-400 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
				Recently, I've focused on the intersection of **Enterprise Integration and Generative AI**, implementing agentic workflows and RAG systems to accelerate architectural delivery and automated quality engineering.
			</p>
			
			<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-6">Professional Philosophy</h2>
			<div class="space-y-4">
				<div class="bg-white/5 p-6 rounded-lg border border-white/10">
					<h3 class="text-accent font-semibold mb-2">Architectural Pragmatism</h3>
					<p class="text-slate-400">Selecting the right tools (MuleSoft, AWS, Solace) to balance immediate business impact with long-term technological stability.</p>
				</div>
				<div class="bg-white/5 p-6 rounded-lg border border-white/10">
					<h3 class="text-accent font-semibold mb-2">Automation as a First Class Citizen</h3>
					<p class="text-slate-400">From CI/CD to AI-assisted test generation (SDET history), I believe architecture is only as strong as the automation supporting it.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</BaseLayout>
